\par \pard\plain \s0\sl256\slmult1\ql\aspalpha\faauto\li0\ri0\lin0\rin0\fi0\sb0\sa160\nowidctlpar{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\hich\af0\langfe4105\dbch\af3\afs22\lang1025\cf0\loch\f3\fs22\lang4105\li0\ri0\lin0\rin0\fi0\ltrpar{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
Constable Hope of the RCMP had read the full situation report \'96 she knew what she knew. It did not look good. Climate scientists were coming out in droves now, on all platforms, and in startling and clear agreement, for the most part. It was becoming rather impossible to ignore them now, no matter where you went to look or read, online or off. The town was becoming a bit of a downer, honestly. Hope knew the whole thing had to be connected. Hope also knew there was a solution to all of it. There was always a solution, up until there were none. When there were no solutions left, you knew it too. }
\par \pard\plain \s0\sl256\slmult1\ql\aspalpha\faauto\li0\ri0\lin0\rin0\fi0\sb0\sa160\nowidctlpar{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\hich\af0\langfe4105\dbch\af3\afs22\lang1025\cf0\loch\f3\fs22\lang4105\li0\ri0\lin0\rin0\fi0\ltrpar{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
This was of course not the situation report she had been tasked to read by this time yesterday, but it was the one she felt required her most pressing attention, at this particular moment.  }
\par \pard\plain \s0\sl256\slmult1\ql\aspalpha\faauto\li0\ri0\lin0\rin0\fi0\sb0\sa160\nowidctlpar{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\hich\af0\langfe4105\dbch\af3\afs22\lang1025\cf0\loch\f3\fs22\lang4105\li0\ri0\lin0\rin0\fi0\ltrpar{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
She looked at her watch. Her cruiser\'92s lights were still flashing blue and red over the surrounding snowed-in parking lot, but she had become preoccupied with the science article she had read that morning, was now scratching notes into her notebook, and had forgotten to turn the lights off. Or, for that matter, she at once realized before forgetting again, to help the two young men she had just apprehended out of the snowbank and into the back of her cruiser, where it was likely considerably warmer. She liked to keep it at about 21 degrees, sometimes 21.5, if she was feeling generous. Snowbanks were, of course, always hovering around zero, depending on who had fallen into one, and dressed in what. }
\par \pard\plain \s0\sl256\slmult1\ql\aspalpha\faauto\li0\ri0\lin0\rin0\fi0\sb0\sa160\nowidctlpar{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\hich\af0\langfe4105\dbch\af3\afs22\lang1025\cf0\loch\f3\fs22\lang4105\li0\ri0\lin0\rin0\fi0\ltrpar{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
It was twenty-hundred hours, 34 minutes. Hope exited the vehicle, walked briskly to the back of the car, and opened the trunk, where she had several emergency blankets folded neatly in an old cardboard box, took three out, shut the trunk}{\dbch\af0\rtlch \ltrch\loch
.}
\par \pard\plain \s0\sl256\slmult1\ql\aspalpha\faauto\li0\ri0\lin0\rin0\fi0\sb0\sa160\nowidctlpar{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\hich\af0\langfe4105\dbch\af3\afs22\lang1025\cf0\loch\f3\fs22\lang4105\li0\ri0\lin0\rin0\fi0\ltrpar{\rtlch \ltrch
\'93}{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
John Munroe,\'94 Hope called toward the snowbound fellow, who was half-drunk and trying to roll, hands cuffed behind him, slowly up the snowbank, in order (presumably) to make a slow break for the woods, once over the top. \'93Stop moving, you may have a concussion, an ambulance is on the way but Other Main is snowed in, they\'92ll be a while.\'94 Hope tossed one of the blankets over John\'92s wriggling form, who slurred several expletives in Hope\'92s direction, and then rolled back down what part of the bank he had managed to roll up, and ended up once again at its base, though this time at least he was tangle-wrapped in a blanket. \'93John Munroe, stay put, I have to find your friend. I\'92ll be right back\'94. John let out a muffled yell of protest, but Hope had walked back to the front of the car, where its headlights flooded the high bank in front of it, highlighting a large, man-shaped impression, now empty of the man. }
\par \pard\plain \s0\sl256\slmult1\ql\aspalpha\faauto\li0\ri0\lin0\rin0\fi0\sb0\sa160\nowidctlpar{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\hich\af0\langfe4105\dbch\af3\afs22\lang1025\cf0\loch\f3\fs22\lang4105\li0\ri0\lin0\rin0\fi0\ltrpar{\i\ai\rtlch \ltrch\loch
A snow angel}{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
, observed Hope. She vividly recalled in that short moment every snow angel she had ever made, where it had been made, and who she had been with at the time. Some of those kids were gone now, a few others lingered around town, still trying to grow their real wings and take flight to someplace warmer. One childhood friend, whose name should could never recall, was rumoured to have moved to Egypt. Hope could not imagine what that might be like, though she had google it over one-hundred-and-thirty times now. }{\i\ai\rtlch \ltrch\loch
What is it like to move to Egypt?}{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
 Was something the Internet always had opinions about.}
\par \pard\plain \s0\sl256\slmult1\ql\aspalpha\faauto\li0\ri0\lin0\rin0\fi0\sb0\sa160\nowidctlpar{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\hich\af0\langfe4105\dbch\af3\afs22\lang1025\cf0\loch\f3\fs22\lang4105\li0\ri0\lin0\rin0\fi0\ltrpar{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
Sgt. Hope rested her orange-mittened hands on her belt and thoughtfully reviewed the scene, which was still disco-ing blue and red. She analyzed the  deep and frenzied bootprints where John\'92s accomplice had been propelled into the snowbank moments before, near the end of the whole chase scene - before she had set off to slow-chase them across the parking lot covered in shin-deep snow, she had already tazed the large unknown man twice \'96 and the fellow\'92s knife had, in the scuffle that nonetheless ensued afterward, been flung into the middle of the parking lot somewhere, likely unrecoverable until Spring now. The station's metal detector was busted, and Old Feller refused to let the department use his, since the incident with his ATV two Summers back.}
\par \pard\plain \s0\sl256\slmult1\ql\aspalpha\faauto\li0\ri0\lin0\rin0\fi0\sb0\sa160\nowidctlpar{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\hich\af0\langfe4105\dbch\af3\afs22\lang1025\cf0\loch\f3\fs22\lang4105\li0\ri0\lin0\rin0\fi0\ltrpar{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
Hope\'92s hand went casually to her gun holster, and stayed there as she picked her way around the spilled groceries, following the tracks. The bootprints were large \'96 size fifteen at least \'96 and the man who had been wearing them had come at her like an ox. It wasn\'92t characteristic of John Munroe to associate with violent offenders, but when john got drinking, he did a lot of things John would not normally do. The bootprints hit their stride near the treeline, tramped about briefly (looking for the knife?), and then bee-lined for the trees, a metre or more separating each print \'96 the man knew how to run in snow, that was clear. }
\par \pard\plain \s0\sl256\slmult1\ql\aspalpha\faauto\li0\ri0\lin0\rin0\fi0\sb0\sa160\nowidctlpar{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\hich\af0\langfe4105\dbch\af3\afs22\lang1025\cf0\loch\f3\fs22\lang4105\li0\ri0\lin0\rin0\fi0\ltrpar{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
Hope still had the other two emergency blankets tucked under her right arm, the left hand stayed close to her sidearm. The cruiser lights played havoc on the treeline, casting colour and harsh shadow over the scene. A passerby at that moment might naturally imagine that two men had robbed a convenience store for groceries and cigarettes, attempted to run from the scene, became stuck in rapidly accumulating snow (record levels, in fact), and after a short and slow pursuit through the too-large parking lot (failed business development was a problem in Elder Falls), finally been driven not-too-gently into a snowbank by a pursuing police car. This is more or less what happened}{\dbch\af0\rtlch \ltrch\loch
.}
\par \pard\plain \s0\sl256\slmult1\ql\aspalpha\faauto\li0\ri0\lin0\rin0\fi0\sb0\sa160\nowidctlpar{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\hich\af0\langfe4105\dbch\af3\afs22\lang1025\cf0\loch\f3\fs22\lang4105\li0\ri0\lin0\rin0\fi0\ltrpar{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
Hope gave the area one more general scan, saw no sign of the second man, and caught sight of Sommersby\'92s plow\'92s top light rounding a bend up ahead. She walked back to where John lay still tangled in his emergency blanket \'96 he had stopped struggling, and seemed to be falling asleep. \'93John Munroe, time to get up, you can\'92t sleep in the snowbank\'94. Hope put the remaining two blankets around John, and helped him struggle to his feet him by an elbow, and into the back of the cruiser. \'93I\'92ve called Glen, he knows you\'92re ok. You\'92re spending the night at the station, ok?\'94 }
\par \pard\plain \s0\sl256\slmult1\ql\aspalpha\faauto\li0\ri0\lin0\rin0\fi0\sb0\sa160\nowidctlpar{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\hich\af0\langfe4105\dbch\af3\afs22\lang1025\cf0\loch\f3\fs22\lang4105\li0\ri0\lin0\rin0\fi0\brdrb\brdrs\brdrw1\brdrcf1\brsp20{\*\brdrb\brdlncol1\brdlnin0\brdlnout1\brdlndist0}\brsp20\ltrpar{\rtlch \ltrch
\'93}{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
Ok, Hope\'94, is all John Munroe could manage to say, as he cuddled into the car\'92s caged back seat, wrapped in blankets. }
\par \pard\plain \s0\sl256\slmult1\ql\aspalpha\faauto\li0\ri0\lin0\rin0\fi0\sb0\sa160\nowidctlpar{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\hich\af0\langfe4105\dbch\af3\afs22\lang1025\cf0\loch\f3\fs22\lang4105\li0\ri0\lin0\rin0\fi0\brdrb\brdrs\brdrw1\brdrcf1\brsp20{\*\brdrb\brdlncol1\brdlnin0\brdlnout1\brdlndist0}\brsp20\ltrpar{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
