\par \pard\plain \s0\sl256\slmult1\ql\aspalpha\faauto\li0\ri0\lin0\rin0\fi0\sb0\sa160\nowidctlpar{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\hich\af0\langfe4105\dbch\af3\afs22\lang1025\cf0\loch\f3\fs22\lang4105\li0\ri0\lin0\rin0\fi0\ltrpar{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
Sgt. Hope had her RCMP cruiser tucked behind the clothing drop-off bin that stood between the coffee shop\'92s lot and Chester Greene\'92s Recycling Depot and Gardening Emporium next door. Her window was down, and she was catching snowflakes on the lid of her double-triple, watching the alchemy of frozen, sky-borne water turn at once again to liquid the moment it touched the brown plastic. Hope had her bright orange gloves on, non-standard, a gift from her Pa. The car\'92s dash monitor glowed spookily, quietly updating her on the town\'92s lack of activity. }
\par \pard\plain \s0\sl256\slmult1\ql\aspalpha\faauto\li0\ri0\lin0\rin0\fi0\sb0\sa160\nowidctlpar{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\hich\af0\langfe4105\dbch\af3\afs22\lang1025\cf0\loch\f3\fs22\lang4105\li0\ri0\lin0\rin0\fi0\ltrpar{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
Half the population of Elder Falls had yet to get their winter tires installed, everybody was being pretty skittish about getting on the roads. The salt truck was still in the shop.}
\par \pard\plain \s0\sl256\slmult1\ql\aspalpha\faauto\li0\ri0\lin0\rin0\fi0\sb0\sa160\nowidctlpar{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\hich\af0\langfe4105\dbch\af3\afs22\lang1025\cf0\loch\f3\fs22\lang4105\li0\ri0\lin0\rin0\fi0\ltrpar{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
Nancy Nottingham\'92s sky-blue Versa shot by, the taillights winking on suddenly as she once again remembered where she was and who was watching.}
\par \pard\plain \s0\sl256\slmult1\ql\aspalpha\faauto\li0\ri0\lin0\rin0\fi0\sb0\sa160\nowidctlpar{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\hich\af0\langfe4105\dbch\af3\afs22\lang1025\cf0\loch\f3\fs22\lang4105\li0\ri0\lin0\rin0\fi0\ltrpar{\rtlch \ltrch
\'93}{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
Careful, Nance.\'94 Hope spoke toward the retreating taillights continuing on}{\dbch\af0\rtlch \ltrch\loch
.}{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
. Only 10 above the speed limit - Hope\'92s usual threshold when her coffee was still warm. Nancy ran three businesses, and did most of the housework, because Pete had gone full mid-life crisis and had quit his job to become a professional tole painter. Nobody told Pete that tole painting had already come and gone \'96 there was no new boom on the horizon, and no telling if tole painting would ever make the same comeback. Pete had some skill with the jigsaw and brushes, there was no question, but in between holiday Craft Fair seasons there were still bills to pay, and a heater to replace. Nancy had always been the household workhorse anyway. Pete was in \'93I.T.\'94, which Hope took to mean he was trained to make websites and apps. \'93Good luck, Nance\'94, Hope thoughtfully added, as the Versa\'92s lights rounded the bend and disappeared from view, no doubt picking up speed, immediately afterward.}
\par \pard\plain \s0\sl256\slmult1\ql\aspalpha\faauto\li0\ri0\lin0\rin0\fi0\sb0\sa160\nowidctlpar{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\hich\af0\langfe4105\dbch\af3\afs22\lang1025\cf0\loch\f3\fs22\lang4105\li0\ri0\lin0\rin0\fi0\ltrpar{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
Main Douglas was the town\'92s chief entry point, and it didn\'92t much concern Hope that she was perpetuating the cop-and-donut stereotype by parking there \'96 everybody knew it was her best spot to catch the young bucks who on occasion, when things got real boring or tense at home, used the stretch to burn off some rubber and frustration, the moment they left the town limits. Since the town\'92s strip mall had burned down two summers previous, business developers had not yet bothered to return to try again (\'93three times is too many times\'94, the last one had said), and this left the town without the usual hanging-out opportunities for its youth and older youth. Elder Falls had a boredom problem, which meant Hope spent somewhat less time at work being bored. This was alright. She enjoyed staying sharp. She did not enjoy having to pull a gun, but it did happen now and then. She had been overdue the past 6 months, and had been trying not to think about that.}
